elements.text:
Data Warehouse Architecture: Sharded RDBMS
inlcuding AWS Redshift, Greenplum, etc.

Data Warehouse Architecture: Append-Only File System
including Google BigQuery, Druid, etc.

Data Warehouse Architecture: Service-Oriented
aka Snowflake

High availability & redundancy
dependent on individual shards

Combination of distributed
key-value store & file system

Data can be formatted
as necessary

Storage & query resources
are tied together

Indexing required to map
block locations to records

Data from operational stores
must be loaded to warehouse format

Columnar formats improve
performance when access
is sequential

Analytic queries compete
with operational queries
for resources

High availability & redundancy
via triple replication
(increases data size 200%)
